  "time_ut": 1658494445,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dba\u0dd2.\u0d91\u0db8\u0dca.\u0d91\u0dc6\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0d85\u0db8\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dc0 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 4\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "In addition to the IMF money, another 4 billion dollars from America",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe said in an interview with CNBC that inflation in Sri Lanka will reach 70 percent in the next 2 months.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe said that the rising inflation will reach a moderate level by September.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe pointed out that the inflation for the next two months was calculated based on the change in the prices of energy products.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe said while participating in the Street Science program of the CNBC channel that Sri Lanka is eligible to receive 3 billion US dollars under the International Monetary Fund's Extended Fund Facility and it will be received in installments over a period of 3 months.",
        "The Extended Fund Facility is a facility created by the International Monetary Fund to assist countries with balance of payments deficits.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe said that after the International Monetary Fund started providing money to Sri Lanka, the Asian Development Bank and the World Bank will provide another US$ 4 billion to Sri Lanka in addition to the amount provided by the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Taking the current economic crisis as an opportunity to learn a lesson from past mistakes, Mr. Weerasinghe pointed out that the reforms made after the end of the International Monetary Fund program should not be reversed.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe said that the authorities should take this as an opportunity to go beyond a program of the International Monetary Fund. He said that the root cause of the current economic crisis is decades of financial abuse.",
        "CNBC channel stated that Mr. Weerasinghe is optimistic that the new President Ranil Wickremesinghe will be able to carry out the necessary reforms for Sri Lanka. Mr. Weerasinghe denied the reports that China has trapped Sri Lanka in debt."
      ],
